headline.main: KANSAS.; Agricultural and Mineral Resources of the Territory--Its Progress and Prosperity.

docs.lead_paragraph: The subject of Kansas emigration is one which has acquired an interest in the public mind unprecedeuted in the history of the country. In addition to the ordinary questions of pecuniary, betterment which influence removal to a new land, it involves one of such political importance as to affect the nation to its very core, and even interfere with the machinery of Government.

headline.main: LECTURES.; Mr. Milburn's Second Lecture--Red Men and the War of Pontiac. The Struggle With Fortune.

docs.lead_paragraph: A very appreciative audience, among whom we observed some of our prominent men of letters, listened with marked interest to the second of Mr. MILBURN'S "Lowell Lectures." The subject was "The" Red Men and the War of PONTIAC."

headline.main: A MISSISSIPPI SCENE.; Love on a Steamboat--Seduction--Marriage-- Boatmen's Justice.

docs.lead_paragraph: The St. Louis Herald tells this story; A week or so ago, the good steamer Helen Mar--now ice-bound at Rattlesnake landing, twenty miles below this city--was the scene of one of those little romances which will sometimes occur in spite of life's dull realities. We state the facts as related to us by a passenger.
